# Service Layer Rules

Services contain business logic. They orchestrate repository calls, enforce domain rules, and trigger side effects (audit logs, notifications).

## Class + Singleton Pattern

Every service follows this exact structure:
```typescript
import { fooRepository } from '../repositories/foo.repository';
import { auditService } from './audit.service';
import { notificationService } from './notification.service';
import { NotFoundError, BadRequestError } from '../errors/AppError';

class FooService {
    async getAll(orgId: string | null, query: FooListQuery): Promise<PaginatedResponse<any>> {
        const { rows, count } = await fooRepository.findAndCountAll(...);
        return { data: rows, total: count, skip: query.skip || 0, limit: query.limit || 20 };
    }

    async getById(id: string, orgId: string | null): Promise<any> {
        const foo = await fooRepository.findByIdAndOrg(id, orgId);
        if (!foo) throw new NotFoundError('Foo');
        return foo;
    }

    async create(orgId: string, dto: CreateFooDTO, audit: AuditContext): Promise<any> {
        const foo = await fooRepository.create({ ...dto, org_id: orgId });
        auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: foo.id, action: 'create', newValues: dto });
        return foo;
    }

    async update(id: string, orgId: string, dto: UpdateFooDTO, audit: AuditContext): Promise<any> {
        const foo = await fooRepository.findByIdAndOrg(id, orgId);
        if (!foo) throw new NotFoundError('Foo');
        const oldValues = { status: foo.status };
        await foo.update(dto);
        auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: foo.id, action: 'update', oldValues, newValues: dto });
        return foo.reload();
    }

    async delete(id: string, orgId: string, audit: AuditContext, force?: boolean): Promise<MessageResponse> {
        const foo = await fooRepository.findByIdParanoid(id, orgId);
        if (!foo) throw new NotFoundError('Foo');
        if (force) {
            await fooRepository.hardDelete(foo);
            auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: id, action: 'hard_delete' });
        } else {
            await fooRepository.softDelete(foo);
            auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: id, action: 'delete' });
        }
        return { message: 'Foo deleted successfully' };
    }

    async restore(id: string, orgId: string, audit: AuditContext): Promise<any> {
        const foo = await fooRepository.findByIdParanoid(id, orgId);
        if (!foo) throw new NotFoundError('Foo');
        await foo.restore();
        auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: id, action: 'restore' });
        return foo;
    }

    async bulkDelete(orgId: string, dto: BulkDeleteDTO, audit: AuditContext): Promise<MessageResponse> {
        await fooRepository.bulkDelete(dto.ids, orgId, dto.force);
        auditService.log({ ...audit, entityType: 'Foo', entityId: dto.ids[0], action: dto.force ? 'bulk_hard_delete' : 'bulk_delete' });
        return { message: `${dto.ids.length} items deleted` };
    }
}
export const fooService = new FooService();
```

## Standard CRUD Methods

Every entity service must implement these methods:

| Method | Signature | Returns |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| `getAll` | `(orgId, query)` | `PaginatedResponse<T>` |
| `getById` | `(id, orgId)` | Entity object |
| `create` | `(orgId, dto, audit)` | Created entity |
| `update` | `(id, orgId, dto, audit)` | Updated entity |
| `delete` | `(id, orgId, audit, force?)` | `{ message: string }` |
| `restore` | `(id, orgId, audit)` | Restored entity |
| `bulkDelete` | `(orgId, dto, audit)` | `{ message: string }` |

## Audit Logging

- Call `auditService.log()` after every successful mutation.
- Fire-and-forget: `auditService.log()` never throws. Do NOT wrap in try/catch.
- Pass `AuditContext` from controller: `{ orgId, userId, userEmail }`.
- Include `oldValues` and `newValues` for updates and status changes.

## Notification Integration

For real-time events (comments, assignments), call `notificationService`:
```typescript
// In controller, get Socket.IO instance:
const io = req.app.get('io');

// Pass to service:
await workOrderService.addComment(woId, orgId, dto, audit, io);

// In service:
notificationService.notifyCommentAdded({ workOrder, commenter, io });
```

Socket.IO rooms: `user_${userId}` for targeted notifications.

## Status Transitions

For entities with state machines (e.g., Work Orders), validate transitions in the service:
```typescript
import { WO_STATUS_TRANSITIONS } from '../constants/workOrder';

async updateStatus(id, orgId, dto, audit) {
    const wo = await repository.findByIdAndOrg(id, orgId);
    if (!wo) throw new NotFoundError('Work Order');

    const allowed = WO_STATUS_TRANSITIONS[wo.status] || [];
    if (!allowed.includes(dto.status)) {
        throw new BadRequestError(`Cannot transition from '${wo.status}' to '${dto.status}'`);
    }

    // Role-based restrictions
    if (['completed', 'cancelled'].includes(dto.status)) {
        const isManager = audit.userRole && ['super_admin', 'org_admin', 'facility_manager'].includes(audit.userRole);
        if (!isManager) throw new ForbiddenError('Only managers can complete or cancel work orders');
    }

    await wo.update({ status: dto.status, ... });
    auditService.log({ ...audit, action: 'status_change', oldValues: { status: wo.status }, newValues: { status: dto.status } });
}
```

## Error Throwing

Services throw typed errors. Never return error objects.
- `throw new NotFoundError('Work Order')` -- entity not found
- `throw new BadRequestError('Invalid status transition')` -- business rule violation
- `throw new ForbiddenError('Only managers can approve')` -- permission denied
- `throw new ConflictError('Email already registered')` -- duplicate resource

## Org Scoping

- `orgId: string | null` -- `null` means no org filter (super admin).
- Pass `orgId` through to repository methods. Repository handles conditional WHERE.

## Transaction Usage

For operations involving multiple tables (inventory deduction, bulk status changes):
```typescript
import sequelize from '../config/database';

async deductInventory(woId, orgId, items, audit) {
    await sequelize.transaction(async (t) => {
        for (const item of items) {
            const invItem = await inventoryRepository.findByIdWithLock(item.id, t);
            if (invItem.quantity < item.quantity) throw new BadRequestError('Insufficient stock');
            await invItem.update({ quantity: invItem.quantity - item.quantity }, { transaction: t });
            await woInventoryRepository.create({ ... }, { transaction: t });
        }
    });
}
```
